{
  "title": "DiagnosticReport → note / measurement / observation",
  "notes": "TWO independent pipelines read every DiagnosticReport.\n\n1) DiagnosticReport__note (PER-REPORT, at most one row per DR). Stage-1 view `omop-diagnosticreport-note` flattens one row per report: code_loinc = `code.coding.where(system=loinc).code.first()`, code_text = `code.text`, effective_dt = `effective.ofType(dateTime)`, presented_data = `presentedForm.first().data`, conclusion = `conclusion`. Stage-2 (mapspec/etl/DiagnosticReport__note.sql) emits one row when `effective_dt IS NOT NULL` AND (presented_data OR conclusion OR code_text present) AND status NOT IN (entered-in-error, cancelled, unknown). Columns: note_type_concept_id = 32817 'EHR' (Type Concept, std S); note_class_concept_id = COALESCE(std.concept_id,0) where std = LOINC code_loinc → Maps-to → standard; note_title = left(code_text,250); note_text = COALESCE(convert_from(decode(presented_data,'base64'),'UTF-8'), conclusion, code_text, ''); encoding_concept_id = 32678 'UTF-8' (Metadata, std S); language_concept_id = 4180186 'English language' (SNOMED Language, std S); provider_id = first Practitioner-typed performer; visit_occurrence_id = encounter; note_date/_datetime from effective_dt (::date / ::timestamp — wall-clock, offset dropped); note_source_value = left(code_loinc,50).\n\n2) DiagnosticReport__measurement / __observation / __procedure_occurrence (PER-CODING fan-out via staging.diagnosticreport_resolved, built by mapspec/etl/_resolve_diagnosticreport.sql). The resolve pass walks EVERY `code.coding` entry through cm.fhir_system_to_omop_vocab (http://loinc.org→LOINC, http://snomed.info/sct→SNOMED, …) → vocab.concept(source) → Maps-to → vocab.concept(standard,'S'), DISTINCT ON (id, std.concept_id) preferring LOINC then SNOMED, and records std.domain_id. The three sibling stage-2 SQLs are trivial `WHERE std_domain='Measurement'|'Observation'|'Procedure'` filters; surrogate PK = stringToId(DR.id || '|' || std_concept_id). Note-domain codings (document-type LOINCs) stay in the resolved table but match none of the three routers — they are captured only by the per-report note edge (see _resolve_diagnosticreport.sql lines 17-20).\n\nGrounding: all concept_ids verified in live vocab.concept (32817 EHR, 32678 UTF-8, 4180186 English language, 32856 Lab, 3030023 History and physical note, 3041851 Evaluation + Plan note, 3026023 Comprehensive metabolic 2000 panel [Measurement], 40758878 PHQ-2 [Observation]). The measurement variant (24323-8→3026023) and observation variant (55757-9→40758878) are real Synthea reports cross-checked against cdm_ours_fhir.measurement / cdm_ours_fhir.observation actual output. Both LOINC codes are themselves standard so src_concept_id == std_concept_id. Synthea writes lab DRs with an Organization performer (provider_id NULL); variant (c) keeps the real Organization-performer shape, variant (a)/(e) add a Practitioner performer to exercise provider_id.\n\nTimezone: every column here casts ::timestamp / ::date, so a `+01:00` source keeps wall-clock local time (the offset is dropped, NOT converted to UTC).",
